Ask HN: I've Built a DHT Torrent Sniffer and Search Engine. Should I Release?
text:
Recently I was researching about DHTs and developed a DHT Sniffer in Go which connects to some known DHT Routers and sniffs all the annoucements. I've quickly added ZincSearch and it is now basically a search engine which can search for hashes, name or files contained in the torrents. It is able to index around 5-10k annoucements per second, so the index grows quite fast.

Now, I am thinking about releasing it as open-source for others to study, but not sure if I should, because it might be used for "evil".

Ask HN: Debugging – Anyone use debuggers these days?
text:
I haven't use any debugger since i stopped using C++ , C , Java or Donet , and that was since I started using Dynamic Langs : Python + Javascript ( 2007-2008) for all the developments.

There are some great debugger integrationd done by VSCode for Python , Javascript but i haven't see any of those used by developer community these days since code is getting much cleaner and simpler.

Anyone still use Debuggers?

Ask HN: Any forum/community dedicated to software and DevOps?
text:
I found Hackernews is the best in tech related news and forum with actual valuable discussions threads going on with no shilling and without fear of losing face .

- Reddit was once such a place but now it is quite gone , with only echo chambers due to nature serious moderation of down-votes - people afraid to go against `Popular opinion` . And /r/Programming or /r/Python is full of new people , just want to learn to program these days so cannot go into serious tech discussions.

- Medium needs subscriptions just to read some popular articles.

Dev.to is not bad , but not much discussions going on , its more of a site to shill and quite Bloggy where i am looking for discussions.

Stackoverflow and Quora are not included in the list since they are Question and Answer.

I am looking for a discussion community with moderation style of HN - That is focused on Programming , Software Development , Devops , Architecture , good principles , etc.
